st of that scholarship has focused on specific issues or selected countries. This book aims to lay the groundwork for a comprehensive, in-depth understanding of Asian security by investigating conceptions of security in sixteen Asian countries. The book undertakes an ethnographic, country-by-country study of how Asian states conceive of their security. For each country, it identifies and explains the security concerns and behavior of central decision makers, asking who or what is to be protected, against what potential threats, and how security policies have changed over time. This inside-out or bottom-up approach facilitates both identification of similarities and differences in the security thinking and practice of Asian countries and exploration of their consequences. The crucial insights into the dynamics of international security in the region provided by this approach can form the basis for further inquiry, including debates about the future of the region.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / General.2bisacsh1 aAlagappa, Muthiah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlagappa, Muthiah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCase, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhong, Cho-Oon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPabottingi, Mochtar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSidel, John T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSukatipan, Saitip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVasavakul, Thaveeporn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYawnghwe, Chao-Tzang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitl